# Configuration Guidance

## Next.js Config
Keep config minimal and explicit. Example stable settings in [next.config.ts](mdc:next.config.ts):
```ts
/** @type {import('next').NextConfig} */
const nextConfig = {
  bundlePagesRouterDependencies: true,
  serverExternalPackages: [],
  experimental: {
    staleTimes: { dynamic: 30, static: 180 },
  },
}
export default nextConfig
```

## TypeScript Config
Align with strict, modern TS in [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json):
```json
{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "strict": true,
    "target": "ES2022",
    "lib": ["dom", "dom.iterable", "esnext"],
    "jsx": "preserve",
    "module": "esnext",
    "moduleResolution": "bundler",
    "noEmit": true,
    "paths": { "@/*": ["./src/*"] }
  }
}
```

